<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563DA32D57FDBED63C" blockId="13.[136,1452,1346,1841]" box="[136,597,1346,1373]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
<heading id="D0B181CB815745563DA32D57FDBED63C" bold="true" box="[136,597,1346,1373]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563DA32D57FDBED63C" bold="true" box="[136,597,1346,1373]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563DA32D57FEA5D63C" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Franchet" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[136,334,1346,1373]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capusii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563DA32D57FEA5D63C" bold="true" box="[136,334,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia capusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is new to 
<collectingCountry id="F3517637815745563CE82D57FDBED63C" box="[451,597,1346,1372]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C652C815745563DA32D73FC35D51C" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563DA32D73FC35D51C" blockId="13.[136,1452,1346,1841]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563DA32D73FEA5D6E0" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Franchet" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[136,334,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capusii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563DA32D73FEA5D6E0" box="[136,334,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia capusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species widely distributed in Mountain Middle Asia, Tian-Shan and Pamir-Alay. In South 
<collectingCountry id="F3517637815745563DA32D9FFF12D6C4" box="[136,249,1418,1444]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, it occurs up to the Afghan border but has not been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F3517637815745563ECB2D9FFB82D6C4" box="[992,1129,1418,1444]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B5681574556395C2D9FFADBD6C4" author="Rechinger, K. H." box="[1143,1328,1418,1444]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" pagination="236 - 257" refId="ref10656" refString="Rechinger, K. H. (1987) Bunium. In: Hedge, I. C., Lamond, J. M., Rechinger, K. H., et al. (1987) Umbelliferae. In: Rechinger, K. H. (Ed.) Flora iranica, vol. 162. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz, Austria, pp. 236 - 257." type="book chapter" year="1987">Rechinger 1987</bibRefCitation>
). Based on herbarium specimens examined at E, K, MW, M and LE, we confirm the presence of the species in North 
<collectingCountry id="F35176378157455638302DBBFA43D6A8" box="[1307,1448,1454,1480]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563DA32DC7FEA0D68C" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Franchet" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[136,331,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capusii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563DA32DC7FEA0D68C" box="[136,331,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia capusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically distinctive among the other species due to the presence of long (over a half of the mericarp length) and erect (vs. recurved) styles. Our phylogenetic tree highlights that the 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D2481574556398D2DE2FAFDD570" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Franchet" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1190,1302,1527,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capusii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB581574556398D2DE2FAFDD570" box="[1190,1302,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. capusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade is well delineated and supported, but also a genetic differentiation among its populations has occurred. In the absence of any good distinguishing morphological characters, the observed variation in ITS/ETS sequences between the samples from 
<collectingCountry id="F3517637815745563DA32E77FEFAD51C" box="[136,273,1634,1660]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
and from the remaining area can be considered as infraspecific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
